Class ResponseImpl<T>

  • java.lang.Object

  • All Implemented Interfaces:
    Response<T>

    abstract class ResponseImpl<T>
extends Object
implements Response<T>
    An immutable response. Each invocation of a 'withXXX' method returns a new instance, making it safe to share instances between threads, at the cost of some efficiency.
